codeSystems.name: AllLanguages
codeSystems.title: All Languages
codeSystems.description: This value set includes all possible codes from BCP-47 (see http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)

codeSystems.name: AuditEventAction
codeSystems.title: Audit Event Action
codeSystems.description: Indicator for type of action performed during the event that generated the event.

codeSystems.name: AuditEventOutcome
codeSystems.title: Audit Event Outcome
codeSystems.description: Indicates whether the event succeeded or failed.

codeSystems.name: AuditEventOutcomeDetail
codeSystems.title: Audit Event Outcome Detail
codeSystems.description: Indicates more detailed reason for outcome.

codeSystems.name: AuditEventSeverity
codeSystems.title: Audit Event Severity
codeSystems.description: The severity of the audit entry.

codeSystems.name: AuditEventSubType
codeSystems.title: Audit Event Sub-Type
codeSystems.description: More detailed code concerning the type of the audit event - defined by DICOM with some additional FHIR, HL7, and other additions.

codeSystems.name: AuditEventID
codeSystems.title: Audit Event ID
codeSystems.description: Event Categories for Audit Events - defined by DICOM with some FHIR specific additions.

codeSystems.name: CommonLanguages
codeSystems.title: Common Languages
codeSystems.description: This value set includes common codes from BCP-47 (see http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)

codeSystems.name: AuditEventEntityRole
codeSystems.title: Audit Event Entity Role
codeSystems.description: Code representing the role the entity played in the audit event.

codeSystems.name: ParticipationRoleType
codeSystems.title: Participation Role Type
codeSystems.description: This FHIR value set is comprised of Actor participation Type codes, which can be used to value FHIR agents, actors, and other role elements. The codes are intended to express how the agent participated in some activity. Sometimes refered to the agent functional-role relative to the activity.

codeSystems.name: SecurityLabelExamples
codeSystems.title: Example set of Security Labels
codeSystems.description: A sample of security labels from [Healthcare Privacy and Security Classification System](http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/security-labels.html#hcs) as the combination of data and event codes.

codeSystems.name: SecurityRoleType
codeSystems.title: Security Role Type
codeSystems.description: This value set contains example structural roles. In general, two types of roles can be distinguished: structural roles and functional roles. Structural Roles reflect human or organizational categories (hierarchies), and describe prerequisites, feasibilities, or competences for actions. Functional roles are bound to the realization or performance of actions.

codeSystems.name: AuditEventSourceType
codeSystems.title: Audit Event Source Type
codeSystems.description: The type of process where the audit event originated from. Use of these codes is not required but is encouraged to maintain translation with DICOM AuditMessage schema.

codeSystems.name: PurposeOfUse
codeSystems.title: PurposeOfUse
codeSystems.description: Supports communication of purpose of use at a general level.
